author: STAFF WRITERS
title: Jye Emdur among Cleo Bachelor 2015 Australia finalists: Photos
text:
Larry Emdur and his son Jye Emdur at Mrs Sippy bar in Double Bay, Sydney.
STAFF WRITERS news.com.au THIS year’s Cleo magazine Bachelor Of The Year nominees have been revealed and it’s all about Larry Emdur’s hunky son Jye.
The 21-year-old model, DJ and design student is one of 30 men to have made the annual list of eligible Aussie bachelors from a range of occupations.
The son of the popular TV personality, who appears shirtless in the black and white Cleo photo shoot, said his dad did offer him one piece of styling advice: “To wear my hair out. He’s getting to that age where he shaves it so maybe that’s why!”
The dark-haired hottie added that he and his dad are “best mates” and they have “everything in common” so he’d consider letting Larry set him up on a date.
A shirtless Jye Emdur in Cleo’s Bachelor photoshoot. Picture: Cleo Source: Supplied
Jye Emdur is nominated for Cleo's Bachelor of the Year. Picture: Cleo Source: Supplied
Also making the cut was Richard Wilkins’ 20-year-old son Christian, who is often photographed alongside his famous father at red carpet events.
Neighbours star Travis Burns, former NRL star Daniel Conn, X Factor contestant Taylor Henderson, 2014 Big Brother winner Ryan Ginns and Australia’s Got Talent contestant Tim Omaji are also on the list.
Larry Emdur and Jye attend the Chelsea FC vs. Sydney FC match at ANZ Stadium in Homebush. Source: News Corp Australia
The 2015 Cleo Bachelor Of The Year will be announced at an event later this year.
